# YAML 1.2
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or reproduce these results, please cite using these metadata."
title: "RAITG: Requirement-Aware Intelligent Test Generator — Dataset, Pipeline, and Reproducibility Bundle"
abstract: >
  Reproducibility bundle for RAITG, a 4-stage LLM-based pipeline that
  generates test cases from natural-language requirements. v2.0.0
  contains 362 natural-language requirements across four domains
  (commercial web 112, financial services 98, healthcare 102,
  logistics 50); 1,086 LLM calls (362 requirements x 3 conditions:
  unverified, ablation, full RAITG); executable mutation testing
  across 4 reference applications (273 mutants total, 225 killed,
  82.42% aggregate kill rate); and statistics for n=362 (Cohen's d
  = 0.65, Wilcoxon p < 0.0001 paired). Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4.6 +
  Haiku 4.5 multi-model comparison.
